  "texts": [
    "Such a scenario carries huge risks: political preferences are volatile; desirable policy change can be highly unpopular; political preferences are often polarised and do not point towards a clear direction.",
    "While this scenario remains science fiction, a more direct injection of voters' preferences into our political systems enabled by AI polling, is both realistic and potentially desirable.",
    "It is liable to enhance citizens' influence on policy-making and play a role in restoring trust in institutions.",
    "We owe this original distinction to Searle: \"[...] weak AI[...] enables us to formulate and test hypotheses in a more rigorous and precise fashion.",
    "[...] In strong AI, because the programmed computer has cognitive states, the programs are not mere tools that enable us to test psychological explanations; rather, the programs are themselves the explanations.\""
  ],
